abstract: Not surprisingly, Muammar el-Qaddafi helped himself to Libya's wealth, an economist writes, and it remains to be seen whether the country's next leaders will do the same.

lead_paragraph: Casey B. Mulligan is an economics professor at the University of Chicago.
